00:00:03.580 --> 00:00:06.240
How to Get LEED-Certified.

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:10.660
LEED is an acronym for Leadership in Energy
and Environmental Design.

00:00:10.660 --> 00:00:15.830
If you're a building professional, get your
project or community LEED-certified.

00:00:15.830 --> 00:00:25.330
You will need Internet access Test application
fee and usgbc state chapter meeting (optional).

00:00:25.330 --> 00:00:26.330
Step 1.

00:00:26.330 --> 00:00:30.590
Visit the U.S. Green Building Council (USGBC)
site.

00:00:30.590 --> 00:00:36.270
USGBC is an organization promoting standards
for cost-efficient and energy-saving green

00:00:36.270 --> 00:00:37.270
buildings.

00:00:37.270 --> 00:00:40.270
Attend a USGBC state chapter meeting.

00:00:40.270 --> 00:00:43.520
Some chapters may offer help to LEED candidates.

00:00:43.520 --> 00:00:44.900
Step 2.

00:00:44.900 --> 00:00:50.610
Learn about LEED, a world recognized green
building certification system by USGBC.

00:00:50.610 --> 00:00:55.390
It provides third party verification of building
design standards Step 3.

00:00:55.390 --> 00:01:01.120
Go to the Green Building Certification Institute
(GBCI) website if you're a professional preparing

00:01:01.120 --> 00:01:03.780
for an LEED certification exam.

00:01:03.780 --> 00:01:09.050
GBCI administers the certification process
for all green commercial or institutional

00:01:09.050 --> 00:01:10.290
projects.

00:01:10.290 --> 00:01:11.540
Step 4.

00:01:11.540 --> 00:01:16.400
Learn about the different types of LEED exams
including the LEED Green Associate exam, the

00:01:16.400 --> 00:01:20.090
Home Green Rater exam, and various LEED AP
exams.

00:01:20.090 --> 00:01:22.960
Choose which one suits your needs.

00:01:22.960 --> 00:01:24.280
Step 5.

00:01:24.280 --> 00:01:27.050
Read GBCI's Certification Guide.

00:01:27.050 --> 00:01:30.600
Learn how to prepare and submit your LEED
certification application.

00:01:30.600 --> 00:01:33.690
Also learn about the application review process.

00:01:33.690 --> 00:01:34.840
Step 6.

00:01:34.840 --> 00:01:39.860
Enroll in one of GBCI's instructor-led online
LEED workshops.

00:01:39.860 --> 00:01:45.150
The workshops teach applicants how to successfully
implement LEED into their projects.

00:01:45.150 --> 00:01:46.500
Step 7.

00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:51.409
Apply at GBCI's website and read exam eligibility
requirements.

00:01:51.409 --> 00:01:56.610
Enter credit card info to pay the application
fee, then await your exam application approval

00:01:56.610 --> 00:01:58.410
notification.

00:01:58.410 --> 00:01:59.590
Step 8.

00:01:59.590 --> 00:02:04.920
Receive a passing score of 170 or higher and
you'll be authorized for the LEED credential

00:02:04.920 --> 00:02:06.450
title.

00:02:06.450 --> 00:02:10.390
Certificates arrive about 2-3 months after
your test date.

